column5: We usually stop for Breakfast at International Falls. The Chocolate Moose is good however we prefer a place that is a bit faster service, but not a fast food chain. What elese is there that is near Highway 53 and has parking for vehicles with boats.

Hi Babamel2, We stay overnight in International Falls twice a year. We like Barney's Family Restaurant. They have good food, reasonable pricing and are open at 5:00 AM. Below is their information. They are minutes off 53. Have a great trip.Barney's Family Restaurant 1323 3rd St, International Falls, MN Phone - (218) 283-3333Thank you,Larry Mac
We eat at Sandy's or Shore lunch both have good food. Service has been good at both. They are on 53 about 4 blocks north of the Chocolate Moose.
I would go with the suggestion to go to Barney's. Good food, good service, plenty of room to park. Pick up any last minute groceries at the store next door before crossing the border.
Every year we stay at the TeePee Motel going and coming back from NW Ontario and next door is the Shore Lunch Cafe For Breakfast and Dinner good food and good prices

You might try the La Place Rendez-Vous Hotel slightly east of Fort Frances. On the way up to Ear Falls, we stopped here for breakfast last year instead of on the US side. That way, we could be across the border a little earlier. You can find more about it at http://www.rendezvoushotel.com/ . Look on their dining link.

Sandy' good food, parking, good coffee, good service, friendly and the locals get to look you over while your there. If you really want a treat go to Grandpa's in Ranier and order the wild rice pancakes. If you do you'll go back again.
is Grandpa's on highway 11? about how far is it from Highway 53?
WEAwhere in Rainer is Grandma's cafe located, is it allong the highway? How far from I falls is it?
